page.title: 01TARSET FOREST (HIGHFIELD)
page.content: The whole of this block with the exception of a small area to the north which runs into Emblehope Moor and an even smaller area to the south, of cultivated land which is farmed, is covered with forest. The highest point is the Dodd (353m). One forest road runs along the southern margin past the ruins of the original 'Highfield'. From this road, there is a long circular road lying to the north, which apart from magnificent views, contains nearly all types of conifers that will grow in this country.
